\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
4.
 Compliance and Exceptions
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
Compliance with this policy is mandatory for all Information Operations personnel involved in the annual policy review,
 maturity scoring,
 or executive reporting process.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Assessment
\series default
:
 Compliance with the review cadence,
 scoring methodology,
 report preparation,
 and submission requirements of this policy shall be assessed through the internal audit process defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 The County Manager's review of the Annual Policy Review Report,
 as defined in Section 6.6,
 provides independent oversight of this policy's execution.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Enforcement
\series default
:
 Failure to conduct the annual policy review within the required timeframe,
 failure to prepare or submit the Annual Policy Review Report,
 or failure to route findings to the required remediation pathways may result in corrective action in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Policy Implementation,
 Enforcement,
 and Legal Alignment).
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Exceptions
\series default
:
 Exceptions to this policy shall be documented in writing with a business justification.
 Exceptions that would materially affect the annual review —
 including extension or waiver of the submission deadline,
 suppression or omission of required report content,
 alteration of the scoring methodology,
 or omission of the audit program effectiveness evaluation defined in Section 6.4 —
 shall be approved by the County Manager in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.08"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Delegation of Authority and Decision Rights) and the exception management framework established in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 All other exceptions shall be approved by the IT Director in accordance with 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 Oral exceptions are not valid.
 No exception shall be granted on an open-ended basis;
 each exception shall specify a defined remediation timeline.
