\begin_layout Subsection*

\lang english
6.
 Policy Statement
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The ECIO Policy Manual is a living governance instrument.
 The policies within it are not static artifacts;
 they are operational controls that the Department shall evaluate annually for continued relevance,
 implementation effectiveness,
 and alignment with the regulatory and operational environment.
 This policy establishes the structured methodology for that evaluation and the reporting mechanism that delivers accountability to County leadership.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
This policy does not govern the policy change control lifecycle —
 that function belongs to 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.05"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 This policy does not conduct audits,
 self-assessments,
 or control tests —
 those functions belong to 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
 This policy consumes the outputs of both and produces the annual maturity assessment and executive report that neither can produce independently.
 The annual policy review conducted under this policy operationalizes the annual internal review referenced in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.05"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 Section 6.1 and does not alter the review cadence,
 approval chain,
 or change control workflow established there.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.1 Review Scope and Cadence
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The IT Director shall conduct the annual policy review and maturity scoring process once per fiscal year.
 The IT Director shall complete the review and submit the Annual Policy Review Report to the County Manager no later than ninety (90) calendar days after the conclusion of each fiscal year.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The review shall encompass every policy in the ECIO Policy Manual.
 The IT Director shall evaluate each policy for:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Implementation status
\series default
:
 whether the policy's directives are implemented and producing the intended outcomes.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Control effectiveness
\series default
:
 whether the controls defined in the policy are operating as designed,
 informed by the assessment results produced under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Operational relevance
\series default
:
 whether the policy's scope,
 directives,
 and controls remain appropriate given changes in the regulatory,
 technological,
 or operational environment since the prior review.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Workforce awareness
\series default
:
 whether personnel subject to the policy demonstrate awareness of and adherence to its requirements,
 informed by training and acknowledgment records maintained under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.01"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Regulatory alignment
\series default
:
 whether the policy's framework mappings and statutory citations remain current and accurate.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The review shall also encompass all appendices within Chapter 6 of the ECIO Policy Manual.
 The IT Director shall evaluate each appendix for currency and accuracy —
 whether its content reflects the current state of the policies,
 roles,
 frameworks,
 and operational structures it supports.
 Appendices do not receive maturity tier assignments;
 they are reference artifacts,
 not operational controls.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Clarification
\series default
:
 Standard Operating Procedures,
 playbooks,
 and other operational documentation maintained in the System of Engagement are not within the scope of this review.
 The currency of those documents is governed by 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.04"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Policy and Documentation Formatting Standards) and 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.13"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 (Knowledge Management Policy);
 their adequacy is tested through 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The IT Director may delegate data compilation and preliminary analysis to the Assistant IT Director.
 The IT Director shall not delegate the maturity tier assignments or the preparation of the final Annual Policy Review Report.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.2 Assessment Inputs
