\begin_layout Subsubsection*

\lang english
6.3 Maturity Scoring Methodology
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The IT Director shall assign a maturity tier to each policy in the ECIO Policy Manual using criteria derived from the NIST Cybersecurity Framework (CSF) 2.0 Tier model.
 NIST CSF 2.0 defines Tiers as a characterization of the rigor of an organization's cybersecurity risk governance and management practices at the organizational level.
 This policy applies the Tier criteria as an internal scoring rubric for per-policy implementation effectiveness —
 an operational derivative,
 not a claim that NIST defines Tiers at individual-policy granularity.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The four (4) tiers,
 as adapted for per-policy maturity assessment,
 are:
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Tier 1 —
 Partial
\series default
:
 The policy exists but its implementation is ad hoc,
 inconsistent,
 or reactive.
 Controls defined in the policy are not consistently applied.
 Assessment evidence under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 is absent,
 incomplete,
 or shows material deficiencies.
 Personnel awareness is limited.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Tier 2 —
 Risk-Informed
\series default
:
 The policy is implemented with management awareness and risk-informed practices,
 but execution is not standardized across all areas within scope.
 Assessment evidence exists but reveals observations or inconsistencies.
 Corrective Action Plans under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.03"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 may be in progress for controls governed by the policy.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Tier 3 —
 Repeatable
\series default
:
 The policy is consistently implemented across all areas within scope.
 Controls produce reliable,
 documented outcomes.
 Assessment evidence under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:5.02"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 shows predominantly conforming results.
 The policy is reviewed and updated through the lifecycle process defined in 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:1.05"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Tier 4 —
 Adaptive
\series default
:
 The policy implementation continuously improves based on audit findings,
 incident lessons learned,
 KPI data,
 and operational experience.
 Practices adapt proactively to changes in the threat environment,
 regulatory landscape,
 or operational context.
 Improvement activity under 
\series bold
Policy 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "pol:3.16"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"
nolink "false"

\end_inset


\series default
 is linked to the policy.
 Trend data shows sustained or improving maturity across two (2) or more consecutive review periods.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard

\lang english
The IT Director shall document the rationale for each tier assignment.
 The rationale shall reference specific assessment inputs from Section 6.2 that support the determination.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Constraint
\series default
:
 The maturity tier assigned to a policy reflects the assessed state of implementation during the review period.
 It is not a target,
 a requirement,
 or a compliance standard.
 Tier assignment does not create an obligation to achieve a higher tier in the subsequent period.
 The IT Director may establish target tiers as a planning tool,
 but target tiers are advisory and do not carry enforcement consequences.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Itemize

\series bold
\lang english
Clarification
\series default
:
 A policy that has been recently adopted or substantially revised may appropriately receive a Tier 1 or Tier 2 assignment in its first review cycle.
 A lower-tier assignment for a newly adopted policy does not constitute a deficiency.
\end_layout

